@startuml Threat Model Diagram - Intel Forge
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam ArrowColor #1565C0
skinparam ArrowThickness 1
skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #E3F2FD
  BorderColor #1565C0
}
skinparam cloud {
  BackgroundColor #FFEBEE
  BorderColor #C62828
}
skinparam database {
  BackgroundColor #FFF3E0
  BorderColor #E65100
}

title <b>Threat Model Diagram</b>\nIntel Forge Security Boundaries & Mitigations

' Trust boundaries
rectangle "Trust Boundary: Public Internet" as TB1 #FFCDD2 {
  actor "Authenticated User" as AuthUser
  actor "Anonymous User" as AnonUser
  actor "Attacker" as Attacker
}

rectangle "Trust Boundary: Application Layer" as TB2 #E8F5E9 {
  component "Next.js Middleware\n• JWT verification\n• CSRF validation\n• Rate limiting\n• Security headers\n• IP lock policies" as Middleware

  component "API Routes\n• Parameterised SQL\n• Input validation (Zod)\n• Role-based access\n• Response signing" as APILayer

  component "Cron Endpoints\n• Bearer CRON_SECRET\n• Rate limit 10/min/IP\n• 429 + Retry-After" as CronLayer
}

rectangle "Trust Boundary: Data Layer" as TB3 #FFF9C4 {
  database "PostgreSQL\n• Connection pool (max 50)\n• Statement timeout 30s\n• No raw SQL exposure\n• Passwords as <REDACTED>" as DB

  database "Milvus\n• Internal network only\n• No public port" as Milvus

  database "MinIO\n• Presigned URLs only\n• No direct public access" as MinIO
}

rectangle "Trust Boundary: External" as TB4 #F3E5F5 {
  component "Upstream Feeds\n(NVD, KEV, ExploitDB, ...)\n• Read-only\n• Timeout 15s\n• Failure = stale cache" as Feeds

  component "Webhook Subscribers\n• HMAC-signed payloads\n• 10s timeout\n• Logged to notification_log" as Webhooks

  component "LLM Provider (optional)\n• API key in env only\n• 15s timeout\n• Fallback to deterministic" as LLM
}

' Legitimate flows
AuthUser --> Middleware : HTTPS + JWT cookie
AnonUser --> Middleware : HTTPS (limited access)
Middleware --> APILayer : validated request
APILayer --> DB : parameterised queries
CronLayer --> DB : automation writes

' External
Feeds --> DB : feed-sync cron writes
APILayer --> Webhooks : alert dispatch
APILayer --> LLM : optional briefing rewrite

' Attack vectors (red)
Attacker -[#C62828]-> Middleware : <color:#C62828>SQL injection attempt\n<b>Mitigated:</b> parameterised queries
Attacker -[#C62828]-> Middleware : <color:#C62828>CSRF attack\n<b>Mitigated:</b> X-CSRF-Token header
Attacker -[#C62828]-> CronLayer : <color:#C62828>Leaked CRON_SECRET\n<b>Mitigated:</b> rate limit 10/min
Attacker -[#C62828]-> Middleware : <color:#C62828>JWT forgery\n<b>Mitigated:</b> DB re-fetch every request
Attacker -[#C62828]-> Middleware : <color:#C62828>Brute force\n<b>Mitigated:</b> edge rate-limit + IP lock

note bottom of DB
  <b>Data Classification:</b>
  • Passwords: NEVER stored raw (<REDACTED:length> only)
  • Stealer logs: login masked (j****@example.invalid)
  • Hostnames: masked (DESKTOP-A****Z)
  • All .invalid TLD for demo data
  • No upstream source names in UI
end note

note right of Middleware
  <b>Security Stack:</b>
  • lib/middleware.ts (requireAuth, requireAdmin)
  • lib/edge-jwt.ts (Edge-compatible verify)
  • lib/csrf.ts (double-submit cookie)
  • lib/rate-limit-edge.ts
  • lib/security-headers.ts (CSP, HSTS, X-Frame)
  • lib/idor-protection.ts
  • lib/ssrf-protection.ts
  • lib/validation.ts (input sanitisation)
end note

@enduml
